	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />I've never tried that before, but it does sound like it'd work quite well.
<br />
<br />I actually fold a standard post-it note in half 4 times one way, pretty much till you can't fold it in half anymore, then I fold it in half 1 time the other way. Do mind you, I don't have the sticky side out. I hold the two ends of the sticky note in one hand, and I place the folded part in between the pins and the plastic, then I swipe the sticky note back and forth really fast. The sticky note comes out FILTHY! So it gets a lot off, I guess. Does that make any sense? It's kind of hard to explain without showing you.

		

		</td>
	</tr>
	</table>


